      "type": "text",
      "data": "<a href=\"https://medium.com/frontmen/art-of-debugging-with-chrome-devtools-ab7b5fd8e0b4\">https://medium.com/frontmen/art-of-debugging-with-chrome-devtools-ab7b5fd8e0b4</a>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<p name=\"644a\" id=\"644a\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.843137); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If you want to use the same devtools debugger to debug your node applications, you can easily do so by invoking your node script with&nbsp;<code class=\"markup--code markup--p-code\" style=\"font-family: Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588); padding: 3px 4px; margin-right: 2px; margin-left: 2px; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">--inspect-brk</code>&nbsp;flag.</p><pre name=\"8eb1\" id=\"8eb1\" class=\"graf graf--pre graf-after--p\" style=\"overflow: auto; font-family: Menlo, Monaco, &quot;Courier New&quot;, Courier, monospace; font-size: 16px; margin-top: 43px; margin-bottom: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588); padding: 20px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.843137); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;\">node --inspect-brk script.js</pre><p name=\"d8b8\" id=\"d8b8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--pre\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.843137); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Go to chrome://inspect. Your node session should appear as one of the remote targets that you can inspect.</p><p name=\"84d4\" id=\"84d4\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.843137); font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Also, in devtools you will see a green node icon, clicking on which will fire up the chrome debugger for the node session.</p>"
    }
  ]
}